 Advanced startup options
 
 f8 - advanced startup options
 
 safe mode - most basic possible mode

 Review 
	- During tthe boot process,press F8 to open the
	advanced startuo options menu.
	
	- from the advanced startup options menu, you can start various
	safe modes, vga modes, and use the last known good configurations
	
	- The startup options vary slightly between each versions of windows.
	
	To use old school f8 to get on advanced startup options
	open a cmd
	> bcedit /set {default} bootmenupolicy legacy
	
	Review
	- windows can autolaunch startup options
	- use recovery environment to access startuo options in windows 8
	- shift-restart to access startup in windows 10